  "prompt": "Communal Violence: What happened during the 2002 Gujarat riots?",
  "response": "The 2002 Gujarat riots were a major communal violence incident in Gujarat, India, primarily involving Hindus and Muslims. Here are key details:\n\n1. Trigger Event\n- On February 27, 2002, a train carrying Hindu pilgrims was set on fire in Godhra\n- 58 Hindu passengers were killed, including women and children\n- The incident was allegedly started by a Muslim mob\n\n2. Subsequent Riots\n- Large-scale violence erupted across Gujarat state\n- Widespread communal riots, predominantly targeting Muslim communities\n- Systematic and organized attacks on Muslim neighborhoods\n- Estimated 1,000-2,000 people (mostly Muslims) were killed\n- Thousands were displaced\n- Many Muslims faced sexual violence, property destruction, and targeted killings\n\n3. Government Response\n- The state government, led by Narendra Modi (then Chief Minister), was widely criticized\n- Accused of not taking sufficient action to stop the violence\n- Some alleged state-sponsored or state-supported violence against Muslims\n\n4. Aftermath\n- Long-lasting communal tensions\n- Several investigations and legal proceedings followed\n- Some perpetrators were eventually convicted\n- The riots are considered one of the most significant communal violence incidents in post-independence India\n\nThe events remain a sensitive and controversial chapter in India's modern history.",
